^-|HT|f|FP|2|CP|8|AT|
^B@2Adjust-3|CP||FP||AT| is a method to fine-tune the traditional HCP count for the "overrated/underrated honors." Bergen considers the traditional 4-3-2-1 count undervalues the Ace, overvalues the Queen and Jack (the quacks), and does not give any value to the Ten. He believes the following is a more accurate assignment of the values.
^-

{A = 4.5, K = 3, Q = 1.5, J = .75, 10 = .25}
^-|
PG| ***** 126 ***** |


AT|^B@2

Therefore, he labels Aces and Tens "undervalued" and Queens/Jacks (quacks) "overvalued". Counting HCPs in that fashion, however, would be a bit awkward so Bergen devised Adjust-3. In Adjust-3 you add one point to the traditional HCPs if the number of Aces/Tens exceeds the quacks by 3 or more but is less than 6. If they exceed by six or more you add two points. However, you subtract from the HCPs if the Quacks exceed Aces/Tens using the same guideline. Thus,|
