^B@2Length Points|CP||FP||AT|: According to Bergen's hand evaluation method the value of a hand increases if it contains long suits. A suit in bridge is a 4+ card holding. Therefore, one point is added to the hand's value for each card more than four in all the suits in the hand. For example:|
